        <section xml:id="couple">
            <title>Propulsion torque<indexterm>
                    <primary>Propulsion</primary>
                    <secondary>Torque</secondary>
                </indexterm></title>
            <para>The torque required depends directly on the diameter of the wheels and the maximum
                resistance force. Power, on the other hand, depends on the torque and rotational
                speed of the wheels, or on the forward speed and resistance force.</para>
            <para>The total force required for the movement is 180N. However, it is evenly
                distributed over all 4-wheel drive. It is therefore 45N per wheel</para>
            <equation>
                <title>Maximum torque per motor</title>
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mi>T</mi>
                    <mo>=</mo>
                    <msub>
                        <mi>F</mi>
                        <mrow>
                            <mi>r</mi>
                            <mi>r</mi>
                        </mrow>
                    </msub>
                    <mo>&#xB7;</mo>
                    <mi>r</mi>
                    <mo>=</mo>
                    <mn>45</mn>
                    <mo>&#xB7;</mo>
                    <mn>0</mn>
                    <mo>,</mo>
                    <mn>15</mn>
                    <mo>=</mo>
                    <mn>6</mn>
                    <mo>,</mo>
                    <mn>75</mn>
                    <mi>N</mi>
                    <mi>m</mi>
                </math>
            </equation>
            <para>This represents the total torque. For 4 motors, the torque per motor is a maximum
                of <emphasis role="bold">6.75Nm</emphasis>.</para>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="puissance">
            <title>Propulsion power<indexterm>
                    <primary>Propulsion</primary>
                    <secondary>Power</secondary>
                </indexterm></title>
            <para>The power required to propel the mower, according to the basic specifications,
                is:</para>
            <equation>
                <title>Required power</title>
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mi>P</mi>
